Ford Motor Co To Recall 3,500 Sedans, SUVs To Fix Fuel Tanks-Reuters
Tuesday, 26 Mar 2013 08:18pm EDT
Reuters reported that Ford Motor Co said that it will recall about 3,500 Taurus, Explorer and Lincoln MKS vehicles around the world to repair fuel tanks equipped with an improperly molded seam. The tanks with these seams may leak after a severe crash, Ford said. As of February 28, 2013 the U.S. automaker received six reports of tanks with a fuel odor or leak due to the defect.Â 
